Three cubes are each formed from the pattern shown. They are then stacked on a table one on top of another so that the $ 13$ visible numbers have the greatest possible sum. What is that sum?\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
unitsize(.8cm);

pen p = linewidth(.8pt);
draw(shift(-2,0)*unitsquare,p);
label("1",(-1.5,0.5));
draw(shift(-1,0)*unitsquare,p);
label("2",(-0.5,0.5));
label("32",(0.5,0.5));
draw(shift(1,0)*unitsquare,p);
label("16",(1.5,0.5));
draw(shift(0,1)*unitsquare,p);
label("4",(0.5,1.5));
draw(shift(0,-1)*unitsquare,p);
label("8",(0.5,-0.5));
\end{asy}
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ 154 \qquad \textbf{(B)}\ 159 \qquad \textbf{(C)}\ 164 \qquad \textbf{(D)}\ 167 \qquad \textbf{(E)}\ 189$
